repoclient 0.1.1:

NOTE: this client is intended to be installed virtual machine images

1.    Install prerequisites
      $ yum install python-setuptools
      $ easy_install pip

2.    Install repoclient
      $ pip install repoclient

3.    Copy the file file to your home directory
      $ cp /etc/repoclient/repoclient.conf ~/.repoclient

4.    Edit ~/.repoclient and change the repository line to point to your Repoman repository in the form https://HOST:PORT.
      Repoclient will check /tmp/x509up_u%USER_ID% for a proxy certificate to authenticate with the repoman server. If you'd like to override this, uncomment the lines userkey and usercert and specify a location manually.
5.    Run repoclient with the command repoclient.

Repoclient uses grid certificates to authenticate with the repoman server.
Ensure that you have a valid, RFC-compliant grid proxy certificate before running repoclient.
(e.g. $ grid-proxy-init -rfc)

Currently implemented commands:

repoclient list [--all]
repoclient getuser [--all]
repoclient info --name imagename 
repoclient save --name imagename [--(any other metadata tags)] [--force]
repoclient get --name imagename
repoclient delete --name imagename [--force]
repoclient update --name imagename [--(any other metadata tags)] [--force]
repoclient share (--user username | --group groupname)  --image vmname
repoclient unshare (--user username | --group groupname)  --image  vmname


Other metadata tag examples: --hypervisor Xen, --os_variant RHEL, --readonly true
All defaults are set in repoclient.conf, set in /etc/repoclient/repoclient.conf by default (custom may be placed at ~/.repoclient)
